    <!-- Beginner 12-Month -->
    <div id="beginner" class="card article-body" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-8);">
      <h2 style="color:#16a34a;">🌱 12-Month Plan (Complete Beginner)</h2>
      <p><strong>Best for:</strong> First-time aspirants starting from scratch.</p>

      <h3>Phase 1 — Foundation (Months 1-4)</h3>
      <h4>Month 1-2: Core Subjects</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Read NCERT History (Class 6-12) + BharatNotes <a href="/subjects/history-culture/">History Foundation notes</a></li>
        <li>Read NCERT Geography (Class 6-12) + BharatNotes <a href="/subjects/geography/">Geography Foundation notes</a></li>
        <li>Start Laxmikanth Indian Polity + BharatNotes <a href="/subjects/polity/">Polity Foundation notes</a></li>
        <li>Daily: 30 min current affairs on <a href="https://ujiyari.com/daily/" target="_blank">Ujiyari.com</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Month 3-4: Remaining Subjects</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Ramesh Singh Indian Economy + BharatNotes <a href="/subjects/economy/">Economy Foundation notes</a></li>
        <li>Shankar IAS Environment + BharatNotes <a href="/subjects/environment/">Environment Foundation notes</a></li>
        <li>Science &amp; Technology basics + BharatNotes <a href="/subjects/science-tech/">S&amp;T Foundation notes</a></li>
        <li>Begin <a href="/prelims/">10-question daily sprints</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Phase 2 — Prelims Depth (Months 5-8)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Switch to <strong>Prelims-level</strong> notes on all subjects</li>
        <li>Solve topic-wise PYQs (2015-2025) on BharatNotes</li>
        <li>Take 1 full mock per month on <a href="/prelims/">Prelims Practice</a></li>
        <li>Daily: 1 hour current affairs + 1 editorial on Ujiyari</li>
        <li>Track progress on <a href="/tracker/">Progress Tracker</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Phase 3 — Mains + Revision (Months 9-12)</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Switch to <strong>Mains-level</strong> notes — analytical depth</li>
        <li>Practice 2 answers daily using <a href="/mains-practice/">Mains prompts</a></li>
        <li>Revise using Prelims notes 2 weeks before Prelims</li>
        <li>Post-Prelims: full Mains focus — GS paper-wise study</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Prelims 6-Month -->
    <div id="prelims" class="card article-body" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-8);">
      <h2 style="color:var(--color-accent);">🎯 6-Month Plan (Prelims Focus)</h2>
      <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Aspirants who have read NCERTs and standard books, now targeting Prelims.</p>

      <h3>Months 1-2: Subject-wise Revision + MCQs</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Read Prelims-level notes for all 10 subjects on BharatNotes</li>
        <li>After each topic: take MCQ quiz on that topic</li>
        <li>Solve 50 PYQs per subject (topic-wise, not year-wise)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Months 3-4: Current Affairs + Weak Areas</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Last 12 months current affairs: use <a href="https://ujiyari.com/monthly/" target="_blank">Ujiyari monthly compilations</a></li>
        <li>Identify weak subjects on <a href="/tracker/">Tracker</a> — double down on lowest-scoring areas</li>
        <li>Weekly: 1 full mock (100 Qs, 2 hours)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Months 5-6: Mock Tests + Revision</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>2 full mocks per week</li>
        <li>Analyse every wrong answer — maintain an error log</li>
        <li>Revise Facts Corners on <a href="https://ujiyari.com/revision/" target="_blank">Ujiyari Revision Mode</a></li>
        <li>Last 2 weeks: only revision, no new topics</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Mains 4-Month -->
    <div id="mains" class="card article-body" style="margin-bottom:var(--space-8);">
      <h2 style="color:var(--color-brand);">✍️ 4-Month Plan (Mains Intensive)</h2>
      <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Post-Prelims preparation or parallel Mains prep.</p>

      <h3>Month 1: GS1 + GS2 Deep Dive</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Read Mains-level notes for History, Geography, Society (GS1)</li>
        <li>Read Mains-level notes for Polity, Governance, IR (GS2)</li>
        <li>Write 2 answers daily (150 words) using <a href="/mains-practice/">practice prompts</a></li>
        <li>Read 2 editorials daily on <a href="https://ujiyari.com/editorials/" target="_blank">Ujiyari.com</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Month 2: GS3 + GS4 Deep Dive</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Economy, Environment, S&amp;T, Security (GS3) — Mains depth</li>
        <li>Ethics case studies (GS4) — practice frameworks</li>
        <li>Write 2 answers daily (switch to 250 words)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Month 3: Essay + Answer Refinement</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Practice 2 full essays (1000-1200 words each)</li>
        <li>Peer review or self-review every answer</li>
        <li>Integrate current affairs into every answer</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Month 4: Full Revision + Mock Tests</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>One full GS paper mock per week (3 hours, all questions)</li>
        <li>Revise all subjects using BharatNotes topic summaries</li>
        <li>Last week: light revision only, stay calm</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

  </div>
